        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "E-Learning",
          "Predicting the Option Selected by Student in MCQ Scenario",
          "Options Selected",
          "10499 learners",
          "Mathematics & German in Lernnavi",
          "Answer Sequences, Questions, Topic Taxonomies",
          "[User Generated Transactions, Questions (and Options), Topic Taxomony for German and Maths]",
          "Most approaches that are SoTA usually focus on whether the answer is correct or incorrect, not the learner’s specific answer - something which can now be better used with attention-based models.",
          "The proposed model uses LLMs to understand content and context of the answers to create student embeddings based on their question answering history.",
          "Users are first organized into learning sessions. Each learning session includes a the sequence of answers given by a student. \n\nFor each question, the options are binary encoded so that it becomes possible to identify what was the answer given by the student.\n\nAuthors created 22 different embeddings: 1 with MLP, 16 with LSTM, 1 with LernnaviBERT and 4 with Mistral7BInstruct\n\nAuthors create a normal KT model from sequences of answers but subsequently incorporate the student embeddings. Main distinction between the models is related to how these embeddings are integrated: \n\nMCQStudentBertCat → concatenates with model outputs before classification, \n\nMCQStudentBertSum → Sums embeddings at input stage",
          "MCQStudentBertCat, MCQStudentBertSum",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{MCC: 0.579 - MCQStudentBertCat with Mistral Embeddings, Accuracy: 0.797 - MCQStudentBertCat with Mistral Embeddings, F1-Score: 0.782 - MCQStudentBertCat with Mistral Embeddings}",
          "Authors compare the 2 different models: MCQStudentBertCat and MCQStudentBertSum using multiple different forms of learner embeddings:\n\n- Dummy (no user embedding), MCQBert, MLP, LSTM, LearnnaviBERT and Mistral 7B.\n\nTesting with the holdout method, the authors found that the representation that concatenates the user embeddings before prediction are the betterr form of introducing hte embeddings. Moreover, the best embbeddings are, unsurprisingly, the ones obtained with Mistral.",
          "Limited interpretability of embedding-based models\n\nSingle context - Lernnavi dataset.\n\nHoldout method"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
